🔧 Fix (step-by-step)
1. Stop and remove old container
docker stop jenkins
docker rm jenkins
2. Start Jenkins with correct socket (Colima)
docker run -d \
-p 8080:8080 \
-p 50000:50000 \
--name jenkins \
-u root \
-v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
jenkins/jenkins:lts

3. Fix permissions (important)
chmod 666 ~/.colima/default/docker.sock
4. Verify
docker exec -it jenkins docker ps

👉 If this works → your pipeline will work

⚠️ One more thing (very important)

Even after fixing socket, you still need Docker CLI inside Jenkins container

Run once:

docker exec -it -u root jenkins bash
apt update
apt install -y docker.io
exit

